entry.def: If you say that something is a re-run of a particular event or experience, you mean that what happens now is very similar to what happened in the past.

example.ex: It was the world's second worst air disaster, a horrific re-run of the runway collision in 1977...
example.tran: 这是世界上第二大空难，是1977年飞机跑道相撞事件的可怕重演。

example.ex: It seems likely that this year will see a re-run of last year's fight over the elementary-school budget.
example.tran: 今年的小学预算问题很可能会像去年那样再次引发争论。

entry.def: If someone re-runs a process or event, they do it or organize it again.

example.ex: Edit the input text and re-run the software...
example.tran: 修改输入的文本，重新运行软件。

example.ex: He re-ran in his mind his conversation with Smith.
example.tran: 他脑子里回顾了一遍他和史密斯的对话。

entry.def: If an election is re-run, it is organized again, for example because the correct procedures were not followed or because no candidate got a large enough majority.

example.ex: The ballot was re-run on Mr Todd's insistence after accusations of malpractice.
example.tran: 因被控舞弊,在托德先生的坚持下重新进行了投票。

entry.def: To re-run a film, play, or television programme means to show it or put it on again.

example.ex: They re-ran the World Cup final on a big screen.
example.tran: 他们在大屏幕上重播了世界杯决赛。

entry.def: A re-run is a film, play, or television programme that is shown or put on again.

example.ex: Viewers will have to make do with tired re-runs and second-rate movies...
example.tran: 电视观众只能将就着看一下已经看厌了的重播节目和二流电影。

example.ex: Thames television announced a re-run of the Benny Hill Show.
example.tran: 泰晤士电视台宣布重播《班尼·希尔秀》。
